feat(ui): apply Apple HIG to home + exam pages

Visible visual change for the two remaining student-facing pages.
Result page was done in 4fcd359; this commit completes the trio.

Home page:
- index.html — switch to .home-page/.home-header/.home-hero/.home-section
  markup. Removed legacy css/pages/home.css link (left only main.css).
  Sections use `hidden` attribute for accessibility.
- exam-list.js — exam cards now use .card.card-raised.card-interactive
  with .home-exam-card structure (top header, meta badges, footer CTA).
  Added tabindex + role=button + aria-label.
- exam-list.js — in-progress card now uses semantic <a> with
  .home-inprogress-item class (HIG warm accent variant).
- history.js — replaced style.display='block'/'none' with hidden
  attribute for a11y. Updated SVG arrow color to var(--accent).

Exam page:
- public/css/pages/_exam.css (NEW, ~9 KB) — Apple HIG exam styles:
  glass topbar, gradient progress bar, animated 3-state timer pill
  (normal/warning/danger with pulse), question card with fade-in,
  option-btn with hover translate + selected ring, sidebar grid
  with status colors via tokens, mobile drawer with backdrop blur,
  gradient submit button.
- main.css — added _exam.css to imports.
- exam.html — switch to .exam-page/.exam-topbar/.exam-question-card
  semantic markup. Kept all IDs so app.js orchestrator runs unchanged.
- Removed legacy public/css/pages/exam.css (replaced by _exam.css).
- Removed legacy public/css/pages/home.css (replaced by _home.css).
- Removed orphan public/minimal-exam-demo.html.

Verified:
- Smoke test still passes (9/9, no behavioural break).
- Visual capture-visuals.mjs renders both light + dark themes
  for all 3 pages without errors.

User-facing summary:
- Apple gray #f5f5f7 background, glassmorphism headers
- Subject-color accent palette in tokens
- Stagger reveals + spring easing (cubic-bezier 0.2,0.8,0.2,1)
- Auto dark mode + prefers-reduced-motion support throughout
